info.headline: Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued January 25 at 11:14AM EST until January 25 at 12:15PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Severe Thunderstorm Warning for... Eastern Wakulla County in Big Bend of Florida... Southwestern Jefferson County in Big Bend of Florida... Northwestern Taylor County in Big Bend of Florida... Southeastern Leon County in Big Bend of Florida... Northeastern Franklin County in Big Bend of Florida... Western Madison County in Big Bend of Florida... * Until 1215 PM EST. * At 1113 AM EST, severe thunderstorms were located along a line extending from 11 miles northeast of Woodville to 6 miles southeast of Carrabelle, moving east at 40 mph. HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. * Locations impacted include... St. Marks, Woodville, Perry, Crawfordville, Wakulla, Greenville, Newport, Cody, Hells Half Acre, Ebb, Lamont, Eridu, Nash, Cabbage Grove, Thomas City, Panacea, Scanlon, Medart, Waukeenah and Wacissa. TORNADO...POSSIBLE HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...<.75 IN WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH
info.instruction: A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon EST for Big Bend of Florida. For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a building. A Tornado Watch remains in effect until noon EST for Big Bend of Florida.
